    public enum ParentalIncome
extends java.lang.Enum<ParentalIncome>
    This enumeration contains all specification for the parental income column of a case.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      HIGH

      This value is representing a high/middle parental income and is converted to the Netica compliant String "High_Middle".
      LOW
      This value is representing a low parental income and is converted to the Netica compliant String "Low".
      LOW_MIDDLE
      This value is representing a low/middle parental income and is converted to the Netica compliant String "Low_Middle".

      • clean

        public static ParentalIncome clean(java.lang.String incomeString)
                            throws WhatToStudyException
        This function is cleaning and validating a String for the nationality property, to enable its use within the network. The income is converted according the World Bank analysis of 2013: Low == < 12.540, Low_Middle == < 49.500 High_Middle == < 152.940, High == > 152.940
        Parameters:
        incomeString - The input String, being an integer bigger than 0, or one of the following: Low, Low_Middle, High_Middle, High
        Returns:
        The cleaned String.
        Throws:
        WhatToStudyException - If the input does not fit the requirements.
